   incr_pmed()/IncrPmedResult promoted to R/incremental-pmed.R; 17 tests (Thm 1
   additivity, Thm 2 reduction); full suite 169/0; CI-clean (S7-generic fun= fix).
   Pushed origin/feature/incremental-pmed (now 6 ahead of dev, 0 behind).
   R3/A-3 (2026-06-19, commit 8e7544f): added estimator-level theorem tests; suite 174/0.
   Finding: Thm 1 is a tautology at the estimator level (tot:=dir+med, incremental-pmed.R:160)
   → oracle test kept; Thm 2 + curve-bending genuinely covered.
   PR-READY but HELD: PR #9 was opened then CLOSED (2026-06-19) to honor the plan below.
   ⚠️ HOLD the PR until you intend to integrate — do not open speculatively.
   ✅ RESOLVED (2026-06-21, dba585c / PR #10): g-score EIF term added. psi (ratio IF for
   Pmed=med/tot) gains dqg*(A-g)*(dir*gamma_med - med*gamma_dir)/tot^2 (T2 layer), mean-zero by
   E[A-g|C]=0 → restores Neyman orthogonality w.r.t. the propensity (CI consistent under
   nonparametric g). Point estimates keep T1-only weight so Thm 2 flat-curve holds at finite n.
   +4 tests (internal orthogonality t-stat, oracle coverage at delta=1, positive SE, 80% sim).
   companion manuscript: ~/projects/research/pmed-modern/02-incremental-pmed.

