✅ RESOLVED (A-15, 2026-06-20): the near-null sobol_pmed() se is now mechanism-pinned by variance
   decomposition (data vs fold-split) — THREE components, not one: (1) a single cross-fitting fold
   partition is ~81% of Var(Δ̂m) near null (persistent n=2000→8000) → fixed by repeated cross-fitting
   (new `reps` arg, mean DML); (2) Δ̂m is normal at the null (oracle-SD coverage ~0.95 → Wald shape OK);
   (3) residual ~0.8× analytic-se bias near null → fixed by `se_method="bootstrap"` (valid, ~1.25×
   conservative). Defaults unchanged (reps=1, analytic). sobol tests 63→77/0. Full coverage-grid
   validation is a large sim → Hopper (run_grid.R/medsim + SLURM array; staged for user launch).
   (Earlier A-12 framing "se_Dm/empSD≈0.56 under-estimate, missing IF-variance term" was the right
   symptom but wrong component — the dominant term was algorithmic fold-split variance, not an EIF gap.)
